            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl1_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/can-i-restore-individual-files-from-an-esxi-or-hyper-v-virtual-machine-backup-with-iperius/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">Can I restore individual files from an ESXi or Hyper-V virtual machine backup with Iperius?</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl1_Label1"><p>Sure. Starting from version 6, Iperius allows you to restore individual files or folders from backups of VMware ESXi and Microsoft Hyper-V virtual machines. It is a very useful and very powerful feature, as it allows you to restore some files by taking them directly from the backups of the virtual machines, without the need [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl1_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/can-i-restore-individual-files-from-an-esxi-or-hyper-v-virtual-machine-backup-with-iperius/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl2_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/can-i-recover-individual-files-from-an-iperius-drive-image-backup/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">Can I recover individual files from an Iperius Drive Image backup?</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl2_Label1"><p>Yes, it is possible to do it very simply. Starting from version 6, with Iperius it is possible to open VHD and VHDX files, and then to extract individual files or folders. Iperius Backup performs its Drive Image on VHD or VHDX files, as well as Windows Server Backup. This ensures maximum compatibility of Iperius [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl2_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/can-i-recover-individual-files-from-an-iperius-drive-image-backup/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl3_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/how-many-remote-computers-can-i-connect-to-with-an-iperius-remote-license/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">How many remote computers can I connect to with an Iperius Remote license?</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl3_Label1"><p>With an Iperius Remote license you can connect to unlimited remote computers. On these computers you can install Iperius Remote as a Windows service for unattended access, and, using the Client Account that you received following your purchase, you can automatically add it to the list of your computers, or your personal address book or [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl3_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/how-many-remote-computers-can-i-connect-to-with-an-iperius-remote-license/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl4_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/does-iperius-remote-support-file-transfer/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">Does Iperius Remote support file transfer?</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl4_Label1"><p>Sure. Iperius Remote has a convenient two-way file transfer functionality. Indeed you can use this function to transfer files to remote computers (upload) or to take files from remote computers (download). The interface is very simple,quite similar to FTP client one, where we have our local computer on the left and the remote computer on [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl4_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/does-iperius-remote-support-file-transfer/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl5_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/cloud-backup-iperius-storage-s3/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">Cloud Backup to Iperius Storage S3</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl5_Label1"><p>Starting from version 6.5, Iperius Backup includes a new powerful cloud storage service: Iperius Storage S3. This service allows you to easily and efficiently save your files on the Iperius S3 cloud storage platform, based on Tier IV distributed datacenters. Online backup is very important to protect your work from hardware failures, thefts, natural disasters [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl5_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/cloud-backup-iperius-storage-s3/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl6_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/how-to-install-kubernetes-with-minikube/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">How to install Kubernetes with Minikube</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl6_Label1"><p>In this article, we will see how to install Kubernetes with Minikube, in container virtualization context that we have already talked about it before. What is Kubernetes? Thanks to container-based virtualization, it is possible to build single applications as an aggregate of several modules or groups of containers. These can cooperate and are exposed outwards [&hellip;]</p>
